<TITLE> Highlights of chief adviser's address </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)  Key points of the chief adviser's speech: 1. Ban on indoor politics goes Monday 2. Pledge to hold elections, if possible, before the Election Commission's specified timeline 3. The national taskforce on corruption will not publish any new list of corruption suspects after September 4. However, the anti-corruption activities of other government agencies will continue in line with the law 5. Tk 820 crore has been returned by corrupt people since anti-corruption drive was launched 6. A final report will be given in connection with the Dhaka University incident, dropping charges against others including unidentified accused 7. No more cases will be filed against anybody and nobody will be harassed over the incident 8. The consumer rights act is now awaiting government's final approval 9. The government will take all necessary steps to ensure shopping in a festive mood during the Ramadan 10. BDR's dal-bhat programme has been strengthened to keep the prices lower in the retail market 11. Another 200 megawatt power generation by December, 370 MW more by June 12. Tk 2,100 crore from the budgetary allocation being used to repair the physical infrastructure damaged by floods 13. The armed forces are sincere about providing assistance to establish true democracy through free, fair and credible elections. bdnews24.c
